The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Adekunle files complaint against Md. Sp.
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: Habib Adekunle, Mohammedan Sportings Nigerian recruit, has complained to the All India Football Federation (AIFF) that he is yet to receive payment to the tune of Rs 4 lakh. The AIFF has directed the letter to the IFA, seeking an explanation from the club  within seven days of receipt  as to why Adekunles dues havent been cleared. As per Adekunles letter, he was contracted with Mohammedan Sporting last year for a yearly fee of Rs 5.5 lakh. He was handed over a cheque for Rs 2.25 lakh (dated June 25, 2003) as advance, but it bounced. Following several pleas, he was paid a total of Rs 1.5 lakh till October 2003. Mohammedan Sporting secretary Sultan Ahmed did concede that the cheque had bounced, but denied the player had only been paid Rs 1.5 lakh thereafter. After the cheque bounced, we have paid him a total of Rs 2.46 lakh in five instalments I have documents to prove it.  Pari likely on lien Meanwhile, Mohammedan Sporting coach Jamshed Nassiri said that a Bengal Mumbai Football Club player is set to be taken on lien during the second leg of the NFL. Coach Jamshed Nassiri felt his forwardline needs more attention.  Copyright 
